inline and block elements

inline - show data in the line - like text --->
span, a... and more

block - take all the space horizontally and display items on below the other
ul, p ...


fonts - properties and selectors

** font-family / font-face (sans-serif, Arial)--> sets the font of the page
font-family: "Times New Roman" - when name has spaces if should be in quotes
font-family: Arial, Helvetica (sequence of shrifts) --> withoout quotes

example:
in css file:
@font-face {
    font-family: "Open Sans";
    src: url("/fonts/opensans.woff") format("woff")
}
in html:
<p style="font-family: Open Sans">Open Sans Demo</p>

** font-size / line-height (18pt)--> the size of the text
with 1px = 0.75pt / or pt or em
em - size of the text depending on the space of the parent / container --> resizable

rem -- size depending on the html size of the document

font-weight ( bold) - how bold should be the text
font-style (italic) --> the type of the shrift
font-variant (SmallCaps) --> makes small letters look like big

** text-allign: left / right/ center/ justify;
** line-height: in px, pt, em or rem
** letter-spacing: in px or normal ot restore
** text-decoration: line-through, underline;
** text-indent: in px - moves the first line of text to lef or right 
** text-overflow: clip; when we run out of space for the text it adds '...' at the back

** text-transform: capitalize / uppercase / lowercase - transforms the text

** word-break: defines how the word should break when reaching the end ogf the line
normal, break-all

** text-shadow: to add a shadow of the text
** background-color: transparent, navy;

** cursor: pointer, move, none, col-size --> 
changes the cursor when hovering

** outline: px dotted color -- adds an outline to our text



